Note:
==============================================================================
MARKUP SELECTOR ENGINE - Matches CSS Selectors against the Element AST
==============================================================================

This module is the matching engine that pairs the CSS Selector AST defined
in compiler/frontend/primitives/style/selector.runa with the Element AST
defined in compiler/frontend/primitives/markup/element.runa.  The parser
+ specificity calculator live in style/selector.runa; the matcher and
the query-all driver live here so the markup substrate can be used
without pulling in the style subsystem when matching is unused.

Matching semantics follow W3C Selectors Level 4
(https://www.w3.org/TR/selectors-4/).  Combinators are evaluated
right-to-left per the algorithm in section 4.  Pseudo-classes implemented:

  :hover, :focus, :active            -- evaluated as always-false unless the
                                        caller has set the corresponding
                                        state flag on the element (state
                                        flags are application concerns)
  :first-child, :last-child          -- structural position in parent
  :nth-child(An+B)                   -- per section 14.4
  :not(simple-selector)              -- recursive non-match
  :has(selector)                     -- recursive presence test (Level 4)
  :empty                             -- no children
  :root                              -- element has no parent

The matcher is iterative; it allocates only when descending into a
combinator's leftward partner via element ancestor / preceding-sibling
chains and produces stable results in O(depth * combinator-count *
average-selector-length) per call.
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_primitive.runa" as StringPrim
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/string_builder.runa" as SB
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/char_core.runa" as Char
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/markup/element.runa" as Elem
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/style/selector.runa" as Sel

Note: ============================================================================
Note: TAG MIRRORS - kept in lockstep with style/selector.runa
Note: ============================================================================

Constant MS_KIND_UNIVERSAL as Integer is 1
Constant MS_KIND_TYPE as Integer is 2
Constant MS_KIND_CLASS as Integer is 3
Constant MS_KIND_ID as Integer is 4
Constant MS_KIND_ATTRIBUTE as Integer is 5
Constant MS_KIND_PSEUDO_CLASS as Integer is 6
Constant MS_KIND_PSEUDO_ELEMENT as Integer is 7
Constant MS_KIND_COMPOUND as Integer is 8
Constant MS_KIND_COMPLEX as Integer is 9
Constant MS_KIND_LIST as Integer is 10
Constant MS_KIND_COMBINATOR as Integer is 11

Constant MS_COMB_DESCENDANT as Integer is 0
Constant MS_COMB_CHILD as Integer is 1
Constant MS_COMB_ADJACENT as Integer is 2
Constant MS_COMB_GENERAL as Integer is 3
Constant MS_COMB_COLUMN as Integer is 4

Constant MS_ATTR_PRESENT as Integer is 0
Constant MS_ATTR_EQ as Integer is 1
Constant MS_ATTR_INCLUDES as Integer is 2
Constant MS_ATTR_DASHMATCH as Integer is 3
Constant MS_ATTR_PREFIX as Integer is 4
Constant MS_ATTR_SUFFIX as Integer is 5
Constant MS_ATTR_SUBSTR as Integer is 6

Note: ============================================================================
Note: STRING UTILITIES - whitespace tokenization on attribute values
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Class attribute matching needs whitespace-tokenized comparison: the
selector .foo matches an element whose class attribute, when split on
ASCII whitespace, contains "foo" exactly.  This is W3C Selectors Level
4 section 6.5.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Scan the haystack one character at a time.  Whenever a non-whitespace
run begins, compare it byte-by-byte against the needle; if it matches
in full and the run terminates at the needle's length, return 1.
Otherwise advance to the next whitespace boundary and continue.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(len(haystack) * len(needle)) worst case; in practice the early-out on
length mismatch keeps this near O(len(haystack)).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe in both arguments; returns 0 on null haystack.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "ms_token_contains" takes haystack as Integer, needle as Integer returns Integer:
    If haystack is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If needle is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let hlen be proc string_length from StringCore with haystack
    Let nlen be proc string_length from StringCore with needle
    If nlen is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than hlen:
        Let ch be proc string_char_at from StringCore with haystack, i
        Let is_ws be proc is_whitespace from Char with ch
        If is_ws is equal to 1:
            Set i to i plus 1
        Otherwise:
            Let start be i
            While i is less than hlen:
                Let c2 be proc string_char_at from StringCore with haystack, i
                Let is_ws2 be proc is_whitespace from Char with c2
                If is_ws2 is equal to 1:
                    Set i to hlen
                Otherwise:
                    Set i to i plus 1
                End If
            End While
            Let run_end be i
            If is_ws is equal to 0:
                Let run_len be run_end minus start
                If run_len is equal to nlen:
                    Let match be 1
                    Let k be 0
                    While k is less than nlen:
                        Let ah be proc string_char_at from StringCore with haystack, start plus k
                        Let an be proc string_char_at from StringCore with needle, k
                        If ah is not equal to an:
                            Set match to 0
                            Set k to nlen
                        End If
                        Set k to k plus 1
                    End While
                    If match is equal to 1:
                        Return 1
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Substring containment used by [attr*=value] (CSS Selectors 4 6.5.7).
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Sliding window scan with early-exit on first match.  Byte-equality used
because attribute values are treated as opaque byte streams; case
sensitivity is the parser/normalizer's responsibility.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(len(haystack) * len(needle)).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe in both inputs.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "ms_contains_substring" takes haystack as Integer, needle as Integer returns Integer:
    If haystack is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If needle is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let hlen be proc string_length from StringCore with haystack
    Let nlen be proc string_length from StringCore with needle
    If nlen is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    If nlen is greater than hlen:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let last_start be hlen minus nlen
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than or equal to last_start:
        Let match be 1
        Let k be 0
        While k is less than nlen:
            Let ah be proc string_char_at from StringCore with haystack, i plus k
            Let an be proc string_char_at from StringCore with needle, k
            If ah is not equal to an:
                Set match to 0
                Set k to nlen
            End If
            Set k to k plus 1
        End While
        If match is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
[attr|=value] dash-match per CSS Selectors 4 6.5.4: the attribute value
either equals `value` exactly or begins with `value-`.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Equality fast-path, then prefix check followed by a dash test.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(len(needle) + 1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "ms_dashmatch" takes haystack as Integer, needle as Integer returns Integer:
    If haystack is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If needle is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let eq be proc string_equals from StringCore with haystack, needle
    If eq is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let prefix_ok be proc string_starts_with from StringCore with haystack, needle
    If prefix_ok is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let nlen be proc string_length from StringCore with needle
    Let next_ch be proc string_char_at from StringCore with haystack, nlen
    If next_ch is equal to 45:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: SIMPLE SELECTOR MATCH
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Test whether a single simple selector matches the given element.  This
is the leaf of the matching recursion.  Each kind is handled with the
inverse of how the parser populates the primary/secondary/attr_op slots.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Switch on the selector kind tag.  Universal selectors trivially match.
Type selectors compare tag names.  Class selectors look up the "class"
attribute and use token-contains.  Id selectors use byte equality on
"id".  Attribute selectors dispatch on attr_op (PRESENT, EQ, INCLUDES,
DASHMATCH, PREFIX, SUFFIX, SUBSTR).  Pseudo-classes call into the
pseudo-class evaluator.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(attributes) for attribute / class lookups; O(1) otherwise.
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.  Pseudo-element selectors always return 0 because they match
no element (they match a generated box).
@End Security_Scope
Process called "selector_match_simple" takes element as Integer, sel as Integer returns Integer:
    If element is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If sel is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let kind be proc selector_kind from Sel with sel
    If kind is equal to MS_KIND_UNIVERSAL:
        Return 1
    End If
    If kind is equal to MS_KIND_TYPE:
        Let needed be proc selector_primary from Sel with sel
        Let tag be proc element_get_tag_name from Elem with element
        Return proc string_equals from StringCore with tag, needed
    End If
    If kind is equal to MS_KIND_CLASS:
        Let class_name be proc selector_primary from Sel with sel
        Let class_attr be "class"
        Let class_value be proc element_get_attribute from Elem with element, class_attr
        Return proc ms_token_contains with class_value, class_name
    End If
    If kind is equal to MS_KIND_ID:
        Let id_name be proc selector_primary from Sel with sel
        Let id_attr be "id"
        Let id_value be proc element_get_attribute from Elem with element, id_attr
        Return proc string_equals from StringCore with id_value, id_name
    End If
    If kind is equal to MS_KIND_ATTRIBUTE:
        Return proc selector_match_attribute with element, sel
    End If
    If kind is equal to MS_KIND_PSEUDO_CLASS:
        Return proc selector_match_pseudo_class with element, sel
    End If
    If kind is equal to MS_KIND_PSEUDO_ELEMENT:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Match an attribute selector against an element.  Combines the seven
operator variants defined by CSS Selectors Level 4 section 6.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Read primary (attribute name), secondary (operand value), and attr_op
slots from the selector node.  For PRESENT, only existence is checked;
for the value-bearing operators, get the actual attribute value and
dispatch to the appropriate comparator helper.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(attributes) on the element; each comparator is linear in value length.
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Returns 0 when the attribute is missing.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "selector_match_attribute" takes element as Integer, sel as Integer returns Integer:
    Let attr_name be proc selector_primary from Sel with sel
    Let op be proc selector_attr_op from Sel with sel
    Let has be proc element_has_attribute from Elem with element, attr_name
    If has is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If op is equal to MS_ATTR_PRESENT:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let value be proc element_get_attribute from Elem with element, attr_name
    Let needed be proc selector_secondary from Sel with sel
    If op is equal to MS_ATTR_EQ:
        Return proc string_equals from StringCore with value, needed
    End If
    If op is equal to MS_ATTR_INCLUDES:
        Return proc ms_token_contains with value, needed
    End If
    If op is equal to MS_ATTR_DASHMATCH:
        Return proc ms_dashmatch with value, needed
    End If
    If op is equal to MS_ATTR_PREFIX:
        Return proc string_starts_with from StringCore with value, needed
    End If
    If op is equal to MS_ATTR_SUFFIX:
        Return proc string_ends_with from StringCore with value, needed
    End If
    If op is equal to MS_ATTR_SUBSTR:
        Return proc ms_contains_substring with value, needed
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: PSEUDO-CLASS MATCH
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Evaluate the structural and presence-style pseudo-classes that the
substrate can answer without external state.  Dynamic pseudo-classes
(:hover, :focus, :active) require interaction state that lives outside
the markup substrate and therefore always evaluate to false here.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Switch on the pseudo name string.  :first-child / :last-child compare
the element's position against its parent's element-child list (text and
comment nodes are skipped per CSS Selectors 4 section 14.3).  :nth-child
parses the An+B argument and tests the position formula per CSS
Selectors 4 section 14.4, accepting bare integers, the An+B grammar,
and the odd / even keywords.  :empty returns 1 when the element has no
children.  :root returns 1 when the element has no parent in the active
scope subtree.  :not and :has recurse into the inner selector parsed
from the secondary slot.  :hover, :focus, :active require interaction
state that lives outside the markup substrate and evaluate to 0.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(parent_children) for position-bearing pseudo-classes; O(subtree) for
:has; O(1) for the others.
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.  Unknown pseudo names return 0.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "ms_element_position_in_parent" takes parent as Integer, target as Integer returns Integer:
    If parent is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If target is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with parent, 24
    If children is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let ccount be proc list_length from List with children
    Let i be 0
    Let position be 0
    While i is less than ccount:
        Let node be proc list_get from List with children, i
        Let kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, 0
        If kind is equal to 1:
            Set position to position plus 1
            Let elem be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, 8
            If elem is equal to target:
                Return position
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "ms_element_child_count" takes parent as Integer returns Integer:
    If parent is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with parent, 24
    If children is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let ccount be proc list_length from List with children
    Let i be 0
    Let count be 0
    While i is less than ccount:
        Let node be proc list_get from List with children, i
        Let kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, 0
        If kind is equal to 1:
            Set count to count plus 1
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return count
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: AN+B PARSER for :nth-child
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
CSS Selectors Level 4 grammar for the :nth-child argument permits a
small set of shapes: an integer literal (e.g. `5`), the keywords
`odd` and `even`, or the An+B form `2n+1`, `-3n+4`, `n`, `-n`, `n-2`,
`+2n`, etc.  This helper parses any of those forms and returns two
out-parameters: the A coefficient and the B offset.  The caller then
applies the matching rule: a 1-indexed position p matches when there
exists a non-negative integer k such that p == A*k + B.  When A is
zero, this collapses to p == B.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
The arg string is consumed in one left-to-right pass.  Leading
whitespace is skipped.  If the string is exactly "odd" (case-sensitive
in CSS but the parser accepts canonical lowercase) the result is
(2,1); for "even" the result is (2,0).  Otherwise an optional sign
prefix is read; a digit run before `n` is the A magnitude (1 when
absent and the sign is present, e.g. `-n`).  If no `n` token is found,
the leading signed integer is B with A=0.  After the `n`, optional
whitespace, sign, whitespace, and digits form B (default 0).  All
whitespace tolerance follows the grammar definition in the spec.
Result encoding: writes A at out_a (8-byte slot) and B at out_b.
Returns 1 on success and 0 on malformed input.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(len(arg)).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.  Malformed input returns 0 and out parameters are unchanged.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "ms_skip_ws" takes s as Integer, i as Integer, slen as Integer returns Integer:
    While i is less than slen:
        Let ch be proc string_char_at from StringCore with s, i
        Let is_ws be proc is_whitespace from Char with ch
        If is_ws is equal to 0:
            Return i
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return i
End Process

Process called "ms_parse_nth_arg" takes arg as Integer, out_a as Integer, out_b as Integer returns Integer:
    If arg is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let slen be proc string_length from StringCore with arg
    If slen is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let eq_odd be proc string_equals from StringCore with arg, "odd"
    If eq_odd is equal to 1:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_a, 0, 2
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_b, 0, 1
        Return 1
    End If
    Let eq_even be proc string_equals from StringCore with arg, "even"
    If eq_even is equal to 1:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_a, 0, 2
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_b, 0, 0
        Return 1
    End If
    Let i be proc ms_skip_ws with arg, 0, slen
    If i is greater than or equal to slen:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let sign be 1
    Let ch0 be proc string_char_at from StringCore with arg, i
    If ch0 is equal to 43:
        Set i to i plus 1
    Otherwise:
        If ch0 is equal to 45:
            Set sign to 0 minus 1
            Set i to i plus 1
        End If
    End If
    Set i to proc ms_skip_ws with arg, i, slen
    Let digit_start be i
    While i is less than slen:
        Let cd be proc string_char_at from StringCore with arg, i
        Let isd be proc is_digit from Char with cd
        If isd is equal to 0:
            Set i to slen plus 1
        Otherwise:
            Set i to i plus 1
        End If
    End While
    If i is greater than slen:
        Set i to i minus slen
        Set i to i minus 1
        Note: i now holds the position of the first non-digit (or slen if all digits)
    Otherwise:
        Note: ran off the end with all digits
        Set i to slen
    End If
    Let mag be 0
    Let has_digits be 0
    Let p be digit_start
    While p is less than i:
        Let pd be proc string_char_at from StringCore with arg, p
        Set mag to mag multiplied by 10
        Set mag to mag plus (pd minus 48)
        Set has_digits to 1
        Set p to p plus 1
    End While
    Set i to proc ms_skip_ws with arg, i, slen
    Let saw_n be 0
    If i is less than slen:
        Let cn be proc string_char_at from StringCore with arg, i
        If cn is equal to 110:
            Set saw_n to 1
        Otherwise:
            If cn is equal to 78:
                Set saw_n to 1
            End If
        End If
    End If
    If saw_n is equal to 0:
        If has_digits is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let b_val be mag multiplied by sign
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_a, 0, 0
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_b, 0, b_val
        Return 1
    End If
    Set i to i plus 1
    Let a_val be mag
    If has_digits is equal to 0:
        Set a_val to 1
    End If
    Set a_val to a_val multiplied by sign
    Set i to proc ms_skip_ws with arg, i, slen
    Let b_sign be 1
    Let b_val2 be 0
    Let saw_b_sign be 0
    If i is less than slen:
        Let cs be proc string_char_at from StringCore with arg, i
        If cs is equal to 43:
            Set saw_b_sign to 1
            Set i to i plus 1
        Otherwise:
            If cs is equal to 45:
                Set saw_b_sign to 1
                Set b_sign to 0 minus 1
                Set i to i plus 1
            End If
        End If
    End If
    Set i to proc ms_skip_ws with arg, i, slen
    Let b_has_digits be 0
    While i is less than slen:
        Let cb be proc string_char_at from StringCore with arg, i
        Let isbd be proc is_digit from Char with cb
        If isbd is equal to 0:
            Set i to slen
        Otherwise:
            Set b_val2 to b_val2 multiplied by 10
            Set b_val2 to b_val2 plus (cb minus 48)
            Set b_has_digits to 1
            Set i to i plus 1
        End If
    End While
    If saw_b_sign is equal to 1:
        If b_has_digits is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
    End If
    Let b_final be b_val2 multiplied by b_sign
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_a, 0, a_val
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_b, 0, b_final
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "selector_match_pseudo_class" takes element as Integer, sel as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc selector_match_pseudo_class_in_scope with element, sel, element
End Process

Process called "selector_match_pseudo_class_in_scope" takes element as Integer, sel as Integer, scope as Integer returns Integer:
    Let name be proc selector_primary from Sel with sel
    If name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let eq_empty be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "empty"
    If eq_empty is equal to 1:
        Let count be proc element_child_count from Elem with element
        If count is equal to 0:
            Return 1
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    Let eq_first be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "first-child"
    If eq_first is equal to 1:
        Let parent_f be proc ms_find_parent with scope, element
        If parent_f is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let pos_f be proc ms_element_position_in_parent with parent_f, element
        If pos_f is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    Let eq_last be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "last-child"
    If eq_last is equal to 1:
        Let parent_l be proc ms_find_parent with scope, element
        If parent_l is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let pos_l be proc ms_element_position_in_parent with parent_l, element
        If pos_l is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let total_l be proc ms_element_child_count with parent_l
        If pos_l is equal to total_l:
            Return 1
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    Let eq_nth be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "nth-child"
    If eq_nth is equal to 1:
        Let parent_n be proc ms_find_parent with scope, element
        If parent_n is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let pos_n be proc ms_element_position_in_parent with parent_n, element
        If pos_n is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let arg be proc selector_secondary from Sel with sel
        Let a_slot be proc allocate from Layout with 8
        If a_slot is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let b_slot be proc allocate from Layout with 8
        If b_slot is equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with a_slot
            Return 0
        End If
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with a_slot, 0, 0
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with b_slot, 0, 0
        Let parsed be proc ms_parse_nth_arg with arg, a_slot, b_slot
        Let a_coef be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with a_slot, 0
        Let b_off be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with b_slot, 0
        proc deallocate from Layout with a_slot
        proc deallocate from Layout with b_slot
        If parsed is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        If a_coef is equal to 0:
            If pos_n is equal to b_off:
                Return 1
            End If
            Return 0
        End If
        Let diff be pos_n minus b_off
        If a_coef is greater than 0:
            If diff is less than 0:
                Return 0
            End If
            Let r be diff
            While r is greater than or equal to a_coef:
                Set r to r minus a_coef
            End While
            If r is equal to 0:
                Return 1
            End If
            Return 0
        End If
        Let neg_a be 0 minus a_coef
        If diff is greater than 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let r2 be 0 minus diff
        While r2 is greater than or equal to neg_a:
            Set r2 to r2 minus neg_a
        End While
        If r2 is equal to 0:
            Return 1
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    Let eq_root be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "root"
    If eq_root is equal to 1:
        Let parent_r be proc ms_find_parent with scope, element
        If parent_r is equal to 0:
            Return 1
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    Let eq_not be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "not"
    If eq_not is equal to 1:
        Let inner be proc selector_secondary from Sel with sel
        Let inner_sel be proc selector_parse from Sel with inner
        If inner_sel is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let inner_match be proc selector_match_in_scope with element, inner_sel, scope
        proc selector_destroy from Sel with inner_sel
        If inner_match is equal to 1:
            Return 0
        End If
        Return 1
    End If
    Let eq_has be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "has"
    If eq_has is equal to 1:
        Let inner_text be proc selector_secondary from Sel with sel
        Let inner_h be proc selector_parse from Sel with inner_text
        If inner_h is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let descendants be proc list_create from List
        If descendants is equal to 0:
            proc selector_destroy from Sel with inner_h
            Return 0
        End If
        proc element_walk from Elem with element, descendants
        Let dcount be proc list_length from List with descendants
        Let i be 1
        Let found be 0
        While i is less than dcount:
            Let d be proc list_get from List with descendants, i
            Let m be proc selector_match_in_scope with d, inner_h, scope
            If m is equal to 1:
                Set found to 1
                Set i to dcount
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        proc list_destroy from List with descendants
        proc selector_destroy from Sel with inner_h
        Return found
    End If
    Let eq_hover be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "hover"
    If eq_hover is equal to 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let eq_focus be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "focus"
    If eq_focus is equal to 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let eq_active be proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "active"
    If eq_active is equal to 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: COMPOUND AND COMPLEX MATCH
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
A compound selector matches an element iff every simple selector in
its child list matches that same element.  Combinators are encoded
inside complex selectors only, so a compound selector's children are
all simple.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Iterate the children list; on any failure, return 0.  All children
matching returns 1.  Empty compound selectors trivially match.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(simple-selector count).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "selector_match_compound" takes element as Integer, sel as Integer returns Integer:
    Let children be proc selector_children from Sel with sel
    If children is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let count be proc list_length from List with children
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let child_sel be proc list_get from List with children, i
        Let m be proc selector_match with element, child_sel
        If m is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
A complex selector's children list interleaves selector pieces and
combinator records: [piece0, comb0, piece1, comb1, piece2, ...].
Matching is performed right-to-left because the rightmost piece must
match the candidate element and earlier combinators specify how to
ascend the tree to find the prior piece.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Walk the children list from the tail.  The terminal piece must match
the candidate.  For each preceding [combinator, piece] pair, find the
appropriate partner element relative to the current candidate
(parent for child combinator, any ancestor for descendant, previous
sibling for adjacent, any earlier sibling for general).  Recurse on
that partner with the partner piece.  Failure to find any partner
satisfying the piece returns 0.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(depth * pieces) for descendant combinators; O(siblings * pieces) for
sibling combinators.
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.  Malformed complex selectors (odd-length children list
without a terminating combinator partner) return 0.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "ms_find_parent" takes root as Integer, target as Integer returns Integer:
    If root is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If target is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with root, 24
    If children is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let ccount be proc list_length from List with children
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than ccount:
        Let node be proc list_get from List with children, i
        Let kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, 0
        If kind is equal to 1:
            Let elem be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, 8
            If elem is equal to target:
                Return root
            End If
            Let parent_in_sub be proc ms_find_parent with elem, target
            If parent_in_sub is not equal to 0:
                Return parent_in_sub
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "selector_match_complex" takes element as Integer, sel as Integer, scope as Integer returns Integer:
    Let children be proc selector_children from Sel with sel
    If children is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let count be proc list_length from List with children
    If count is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let last_index be count minus 1
    Let last_piece be proc list_get from List with children, last_index
    Let tail_match be proc selector_match with element, last_piece
    If tail_match is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If count is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let current be element
    Let i be last_index minus 1
    While i is greater than or equal to 1:
        Let comb_node be proc list_get from List with children, i
        Let comb_id be proc selector_combinator_id from Sel with comb_node
        Let piece_node be proc list_get from List with children, i minus 1
        Let parent be proc ms_find_parent with scope, current
        If comb_id is equal to MS_COMB_CHILD:
            If parent is equal to 0:
                Return 0
            End If
            Let pm be proc selector_match with parent, piece_node
            If pm is equal to 0:
                Return 0
            End If
            Set current to parent
        Otherwise:
            If comb_id is equal to MS_COMB_DESCENDANT:
                Let ancestor be parent
                Let found be 0
                While ancestor is not equal to 0:
                    Let am be proc selector_match with ancestor, piece_node
                    If am is equal to 1:
                        Set current to ancestor
                        Set found to 1
                        Set ancestor to 0
                    Otherwise:
                        Set ancestor to proc ms_find_parent with scope, ancestor
                    End If
                End While
                If found is equal to 0:
                    Return 0
                End If
            Otherwise:
                If comb_id is equal to MS_COMB_ADJACENT:
                    If parent is equal to 0:
                        Return 0
                    End If
                    Let siblings be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with parent, 24
                    Let scount be proc list_length from List with siblings
                    Let s be 0
                    Let prev be 0
                    While s is less than scount:
                        Let snode be proc list_get from List with siblings, s
                        Let snode_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with snode, 0
                        If snode_kind is equal to 1:
                            Let selem be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with snode, 8
                            If selem is equal to current:
                                Set s to scount
                            Otherwise:
                                Set prev to selem
                            End If
                        End If
                        Set s to s plus 1
                    End While
                    If prev is equal to 0:
                        Return 0
                    End If
                    Let pm2 be proc selector_match with prev, piece_node
                    If pm2 is equal to 0:
                        Return 0
                    End If
                    Set current to prev
                Otherwise:
                    If comb_id is equal to MS_COMB_GENERAL:
                        If parent is equal to 0:
                            Return 0
                        End If
                        Let siblings2 be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with parent, 24
                        Let s2count be proc list_length from List with siblings2
                        Let t be 0
                        Let general_found be 0
                        While t is less than s2count:
                            Let tnode be proc list_get from List with siblings2, t
                            Let tnode_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tnode, 0
                            If tnode_kind is equal to 1:
                                Let telem be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tnode, 8
                                If telem is equal to current:
                                    Set t to s2count
                                Otherwise:
                                    Let gm be proc selector_match with telem, piece_node
                                    If gm is equal to 1:
                                        Set general_found to 1
                                        Set current to telem
                                    End If
                                End If
                            End If
                            Set t to t plus 1
                        End While
                        If general_found is equal to 0:
                            Return 0
                        End If
                    Otherwise:
                        Return 0
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i minus 2
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: PUBLIC ENTRY POINT
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Top-level matcher dispatching on the selector kind.  For complex
selectors the scope (root the matcher knows about) is the element
itself.  Users who already have a document root for ancestor queries
should call selector_match_in_scope.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Switch on kind: simple-leaf kinds delegate to selector_match_simple,
compound to selector_match_compound, complex to selector_match_complex,
list to a logical-OR over the list members.  Combinator nodes never
appear as standalone selectors and always return 0 if reached.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
Linear in selector structure plus the cost of the per-kind matcher.
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "selector_match" takes element as Integer, sel as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc selector_match_in_scope with element, sel, element
End Process

Process called "selector_match_in_scope" takes element as Integer, sel as Integer, scope as Integer returns Integer:
    If element is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If sel is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let kind be proc selector_kind from Sel with sel
    If kind is equal to MS_KIND_COMPOUND:
        Return proc selector_match_compound with element, sel
    End If
    If kind is equal to MS_KIND_COMPLEX:
        Return proc selector_match_complex with element, sel, scope
    End If
    If kind is equal to MS_KIND_LIST:
        Let children be proc selector_children from Sel with sel
        Let count be proc list_length from List with children
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than count:
            Let sub be proc list_get from List with children, i
            Let m be proc selector_match_in_scope with element, sub, scope
            If m is equal to 1:
                Return 1
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        Return 0
    End If
    If kind is equal to MS_KIND_COMBINATOR:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc selector_match_simple with element, sel
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: QUERY-ALL DRIVER
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Return every element under `root` (in document order) that matches the
given selector.  Mirrors DOM document.querySelectorAll.  The result is
a freshly allocated List of element pointers; the caller owns it and
must release it with list_destroy.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
1. Walk the entire subtree with element_walk into a scratch list.
2. Iterate, pushing every matching element to a fresh result list.
3. Destroy the scratch list and return the result.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(n * selector_cost).  Two list allocations; the scratch is bounded by
total element count and released before return.
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on OOM or null root/selector.  An empty (non-null) list means
"no matches".
@End Security_Scope
Process called "selector_query_all" takes root as Integer, sel as Integer returns Integer:
    If root is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If sel is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let candidates be proc list_create from List
    If candidates is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc element_walk from Elem with root, candidates
    Let result be proc list_create from List
    If result is equal to 0:
        proc list_destroy from List with candidates
        Return 0
    End If
    Let count be proc list_length from List with candidates
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let elem be proc list_get from List with candidates, i
        Let m be proc selector_match_in_scope with elem, sel, root
        If m is equal to 1:
            proc list_push from List with result, elem
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    proc list_destroy from List with candidates
    Return result
End Process

@Reasoning
Return the first matching element or 0.  Mirrors DOM querySelector.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Same scan as selector_query_all but bails out on first match.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(n * selector_cost) worst case; often much less because of early-exit.
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "selector_query_first" takes root as Integer, sel as Integer returns Integer:
    If root is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If sel is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let candidates be proc list_create from List
    If candidates is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc element_walk from Elem with root, candidates
    Let count be proc list_length from List with candidates
    Let i be 0
    Let found be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let elem be proc list_get from List with candidates, i
        Let m be proc selector_match_in_scope with elem, sel, root
        If m is equal to 1:
            Set found to elem
            Set i to count
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    proc list_destroy from List with candidates
    Return found
End Process
